summary: (CR SPOILERS RE SOME GOOGLE CHEATING I DID) Because I’m always a huge fan of planar magic I was interested in why these rifts...
body:
(CR SPOILERS RE SOME GOOGLE CHEATING I DID)

Because I’m always a huge fan of planar magic I was interested in why these rifts are popping up all over Xhorhas and I found this which, while I’ve never played those games, fits really well - perhaps that generated some initial rifts, demons came through and created the smaller devices like the one the M9 disabled in Asarius, and one of the consecuted houses is guarding it and lying.

Then again I’d also believe a whole lot of stuff - that dunamancy is messing with the fabric of the planes and started the first rift; that there’s some ancient stuff left over from the Age of Arcanum, who knows.

summary: i love d&d pcs who have one trademark spell that they use even when it wouldn’t do anything or just for goofs like jester’s...
body:
i love d&d pcs who have one trademark spell that they use even when it wouldn’t do anything or just for goofs like jester’s thaumaturgy but what i love even more is when the spell ends up being exactly what they need or the dm bends mechanics so it has more of a flavor thing

like with merle’s zone of truth and how he uses it in the finale as a fundamental thing, less a field in which creatures can’t lie and more of a field that purges what’s corrupted and protects the inhabitants


listen i’m not saying thaumaturgy is going to turn the tide of the final battle but if you think about it you could open all the windows of a pressurized chamber at once and that’ll crunch someone like a fucking soda can
